“Direction” will be our response variable (binary)

plotting variables against each other, using colour as our binary response “Direction”

pairs(Smarket, col = Smarket$Direction)

Logistic regression

uses the glm function, with the parameter family = binomial

glm.fit = glm(Direction ~ Lag1 + Lag2 + Lag3 + Lag4 + Lag5 + Volume, data = Smarket, family = binomial)
summary(glm.fit)

looking at the p-values, looks like none of the variables are significant (doesnt mean that they cant make reasonable prediction) - Null deviance: log likelihood if using just the mean model - Residual deviance: deviance with all the predictors in the model
